### Instructions for translating Universal Android Toolkit ###

First, create a file with the country and language and the file extension should be .lang. E.G: English (UK) would be: en_gb.lang

Secondly, copy the contents from en_gb.lang to your new file. This is because the en_gb file will always be up-to-date, whereas others may be missing some translations.

Thirdly, the files are built as follows:

# ========== Category ========== #

	  windowName:controlName=Control Text ← Translate that.

Here is a "live" example from English to Spanish (Latin America):

 # English (Great Britain), default language for Universal Android Toolkit
 
 # ========== Buttons and Labels ========== #
 
 # Android tab
	  installButton=Install
	  uninstallButton=Uninstall
	  fileManagerButton=File Manager
	  backupButton=Backup
	  restoreButton=Restore
	  exploreRootButton=Explore!
	  connectButton=Connect...
	  disconnectButton=Disconnect...
	  moreButton=More...

 # Español (Latino América)
 
 # ========== Buttons and Labels ========== #
 
 # Android tab
	  installButton=Instalar
	  uninstallButton=Desinstalar
	  fileManagerButton=Administrador de Archivos
	  backupButton=Hacer copia de respaldo
	  restoreButton=Recuperar copia de respaldo
	  exploreRootButton=Explorar!
	  connectButton=Conectar...
	  disconnectButton=Desconectar...
	  moreButton=Más...